  "design_rationale": "Binary columnar storage sorted by l_shipdate (critical filter column) with 100K-row blocks for zone map effectiveness. Dictionary encoding for low-cardinality strings (c_mktsegment, l_returnflag, l_linestatus). Sorted indexes on all join keys (orderkey, custkey, suppkey, partkey) for efficient lookups. Zone maps on filter columns (dates, discount, quantity) enable block skipping. Highly parallelized ingestion uses all 64 cores with mmap input and 1MB write buffers. HDD storage requires zero-copy mmap to avoid repeated parsing overhead. Index building separated from ingestion allows adding indexes later without re-ingesting.",
  "summary": "Columnar binary storage with l_shipdate sorting, 100K-row blocks with zone maps, dictionary-encoded strings, sorted indexes on join keys, 64-core parallelized ingestion with mmap."
